<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="333" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d333">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Sir
                                    <persName type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-04-06"><hi rend="italic">April 6,
                                1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Sir Julian</hi>: In returning to you the
                            Earl of Rosebery’s dispatch of the 11th ultimo, which you kindly left
                            with me, relative to the reports received by Her Majesty’s Government
                            respecting the destruction of the American college at Massouvan, I beg
                            you to convey to his lordship my cordial thanks for his courtesy in
                            communicating the information in question to me.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>